This article is a statement by the President on the one year anniversary of the earthquake, tsunami, and nuclear disasters in Japan. The President honors the memory of the 19,000 victims and acknowledges the resilience and determination of the Japanese people to rebuild stronger than before. The United States mobilized to help Japan, providing humanitarian assistance and disaster relief efforts. One year later, the US remains committed to assisting Japan in their rebuilding efforts. US experts continue to support Japan in dealing with the challenges associated with Fukushima. The TOMODACHI public-private partnership is also investing in strengthening cultural and economic ties between the two nations. The President expresses gratitude for the contributions of Americans and people from around the world who have supported Japan's recovery. The article concludes by emphasizing the unshakeable friendship and alliance between the US and Japan.